column1: # `bulktest -T` template script data file, generated by mk_mupdf_bulktest_script
# Use this data file with the template script(s) for the latest GerHobbelt/mupdf::bulktest tool
# Every line is an argv-cli style record (row), with the following parameters:
# nr.:     %datarow     -- index number of the test record
# PDF:     %1           -- full RELATIVE path to the PDF
# dir:     %2           -- basedir = path part of that
# name:    %3           -- filename = PDF filename part of that one (with .pdf extension)
# base:    %4           -- basename = PDF filename "    "  "    "   (without the .pdf extension)
# cd root: %5           -- path to root of the repo
# Note: latest `bulktest` tool also accepts one-file-per-line input:
# Lines MAY also be a single argument: the full path to the test file.

Sample-PDFs-for-format-testing/testset misc 3 OCR/Theory of Thermionic Vacuum Tubes E. Chaffee (1933).pdf  "Sample-PDFs-for-format-testing/testset misc 3 OCR"    "Theory of Thermionic Vacuum Tubes E. Chaffee (1933).pdf"      "Theory of Thermionic Vacuum Tubes E. Chaffee (1933)"      "./"

Sample-PDFs-for-format-testing/Qiqqa Tools - test collection/56831E9293475B87B10CB53E84AAD11B8455397.pdf  "Sample-PDFs-for-format-testing/Qiqqa Tools - test collection"    "56831E9293475B87B10CB53E84AAD11B8455397.pdf"      "56831E9293475B87B10CB53E84AAD11B8455397"      "./"
